---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Button from '../components/atoms/Button.astro';
import Hero from '../components/organisms/Hero.astro';
import CTASection from '../components/organisms/CTASection.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Roadmap — HPS AI Hub"
  description="What leaked from the Claude Code source, what HPS OS replicated, and what's coming next."
>
  <Nav />

  <main class="main">

    <Hero eyebrow="05 / 12 — What's Coming" eyebrowIcon="lucide:map">
      <Fragment slot="title">
        <span class="accent">Roadmap</span>.
      </Fragment>
      <Fragment slot="lede">
        What the March 2026 Claude Code source leak revealed, how HPS OS
        replicated or diverged from each feature, and what's planned next.
      </Fragment>
    </Hero>

    <!-- ── §05 — What Leaked ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="content-section" data-animate="fade-up">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2 class="section-title" data-animate="fade-up">What Leaked</h2>
        <p class="prose">
          In March 2026 the Claude Code source was decompiled and published.
          Nine internal features were exposed — some unreleased, some behind
          environment flags, some already shipped. The following cards capture
          each feature's status <strong>as of the March 2026 Claude Code source leak</strong>
          and how HPS OS responded.
        </p>

        <ul class="leak-grid" role="list">

          <!-- 1. KAIROS -->
          <li class="leak-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <div class="leak-header">
              <h3 class="leak-name">KAIROS</h3>
              <span class="status-badge" data-status="unreleased">Unreleased</span>
            </div>
            <p class="leak-desc">Overnight memory consolidation engine — orient, gather, consolidate, prune. Runs at 03:00 via cron, compresses a week of observations into a structured summary.</p>
            <p class="leak-hps"><strong>HPS replication:</strong> HPS-Dream replicates the full 4-phase pipeline via Engram MCP + nightly cron.</p>
          </li>

          <!-- 2. ULTRAPLAN -->
          <li class="leak-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <div class="leak-header">
              <h3 class="leak-name">ULTRAPLAN</h3>
              <span class="status-badge" data-status="unreleased">Unreleased</span>
            </div>
            <p class="leak-desc">Multi-phase planning system for complex tasks — decompose, sequence, execute, verify. Internal orchestration layer.</p>
            <p class="leak-hps"><strong>HPS replication:</strong> OmO Prometheus + Metis + Momus provide equivalent planning, execution, and verification phases.</p>
          </li>

          <!-- 3. Coordinator Mode -->
          <li class="leak-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <div class="leak-header">
              <h3 class="leak-name">Coordinator Mode</h3>
              <span class="status-badge" data-status="env-flag">ENV Flag</span>
            </div>
            <p class="leak-desc">Multi-agent coordination where a primary agent spawns and manages worker agents. Gated behind an environment variable in the leaked source.</p>
            <p class="leak-hps"><strong>HPS replication:</strong> OmO Sisyphus and Atlas agents provide coordinator-worker orchestration.</p>
          </li>

          <!-- 4. SKILL_SEARCH -->
          <li class="leak-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <div class="leak-header">
              <h3 class="leak-name">SKILL_SEARCH</h3>
              <span class="status-badge" data-status="unreleased">Unreleased</span>
            </div>
            <p class="leak-desc">Semantic vector search over the skill registry — finds relevant skills by embedding similarity rather than keyword match.</p>
            <p class="leak-hps"><strong>HPS replication:</strong> Planned — hps-ml embeddings will power skill search via FTS5 + vector index.</p>
          </li>

          <!-- 5. Daemon Mode -->
          <li class="leak-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <div class="leak-header">
              <h3 class="leak-name">Daemon Mode</h3>
              <span class="status-badge" data-status="unreleased">Unreleased</span>
            </div>
            <p class="leak-desc">Background agent process that persists between terminal sessions — always-on, event-driven execution.</p>
            <p class="leak-hps"><strong>HPS replication:</strong> OmO Background Agents provide equivalent always-on daemon capability.</p>
          </li>

          <!-- 6. Auto-Dream -->
          <li class="leak-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <div class="leak-header">
              <h3 class="leak-name">Auto-Dream</h3>
              <span class="status-badge" data-status="unreleased">Unreleased</span>
            </div>
            <p class="leak-desc">Automatic overnight memory processing — the system dreams while you sleep, consolidating context autonomously.</p>
            <p class="leak-hps"><strong>HPS replication:</strong> HPS-Dream nightly cron fires the same pipeline at 03:00 automatically.</p>
          </li>

          <!-- 7. UDS Inbox -->
          <li class="leak-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <div class="leak-header">
              <h3 class="leak-name">UDS Inbox</h3>
              <span class="status-badge" data-status="unreleased">Unreleased</span>
            </div>
            <p class="leak-desc">Cross-session inter-process communication via Unix domain sockets — agents can message each other without shared filesystem.</p>
            <p class="leak-hps"><strong>HPS replication:</strong> Not yet in HPS OS — planned for Layer C.</p>
          </li>

          <!-- 8. BUDDY -->
          <li class="leak-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <div class="leak-header">
              <h3 class="leak-name">BUDDY</h3>
              <span class="status-badge" data-status="released">Released</span>
            </div>
            <p class="leak-desc">Easter egg companion mode — a lighter conversational personality embedded in the CLI.</p>
            <p class="leak-hps"><strong>HPS replication:</strong> Easter egg — not critical to the operating system.</p>
          </li>

          <!-- 9. Bridge -->
          <li class="leak-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <div class="leak-header">
              <h3 class="leak-name">Bridge</h3>
              <span class="status-badge" data-status="released">Released</span>
            </div>
            <p class="leak-desc">Remote control interface — manage CLI sessions from a phone or browser. Bridges the terminal to external clients.</p>
            <p class="leak-hps"><strong>HPS replication:</strong> Planned — Flutter HPS Owner app will provide remote bridge capability.</p>
          </li>

        </ul>

        <!-- Evergreen callout -->
        <div class="callout callout-evergreen" data-animate="fade-up">
          <p>
            HPS OS moved to an API-direct integration strategy after Anthropic
            ended third-party harness access — no intermediary harness layers,
            the Anthropic SDK is the integration point.
            <a href="/news">Read the news entry</a> for context.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Hidden Commands -->
        <h3 class="subsection-title" data-animate="fade-up">Hidden Commands</h3>
        <p class="prose">
          The leaked source also exposed six undocumented slash commands.
          These were not part of the public CLI help output as of the March 2026 leak.
        </p>

        <div class="table-wrapper" data-animate="fade-up">
          <table class="cmd-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Command</th>
                <th>Description</th>
                <th>Leaked status</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><code>/ctx-viz</code></td>
                <td>Visualise context window token usage in a sparkline bar</td>
                <td>Internal only</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>/btw</code></td>
                <td>Inject a side-note into the conversation without triggering a full turn</td>
                <td>Internal only</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>/dream</code></td>
                <td>Manually trigger the KAIROS overnight consolidation pipeline</td>
                <td>Internal only</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>/force-snip</code></td>
                <td>Manually free context tokens by snipping older conversation turns</td>
                <td>Internal only</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>/bughunter</code></td>
                <td>Adversarial agent that probes your code for edge cases and bugs</td>
                <td>Internal only</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>/debug-tool-call</code></td>
                <td>Dump the raw tool-call payload for the last tool invocation</td>
                <td>Internal only</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── §12 — What's Next ───────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="content-section" data-animate="fade-up">
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2 class="section-title" data-animate="fade-up">What's Next</h2>
        <p class="prose">
          The roadmap is organised in two tiers. <strong>Layer B</strong> focuses
          on token efficiency and security hardening. <strong>Layer C</strong>
          adds advanced capabilities that extend the operating system's reach.
        </p>

        <h3 class="subsection-title" data-animate="fade-up">Layer B — Token Efficiency &amp; Security</h3>
        <ul class="road-grid" role="list">

          <li class="road-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <h4 class="road-name">HPS-YOLO</h4>
            <p class="road-layer">Layer 7 — Security</p>
            <p class="road-desc">PreToolUse hook security classifier. Evaluates every tool call before execution and blocks unsafe operations without a confirmation prompt.</p>
          </li>

          <li class="road-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <h4 class="road-name">Dippy</h4>
            <p class="road-layer">Replaces Bash AST Safety</p>
            <p class="road-desc">Pure Python AST parser with 14K tests. Install-not-build approach — validates shell commands structurally instead of regex matching.</p>
          </li>

          <li class="road-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <h4 class="road-name">context-mode</h4>
            <p class="road-layer">Replaces /ctx-viz + /btw + /force-snip</p>
            <p class="road-desc">Single plugin that unifies three leaked commands into one coherent context management interface — visualise, annotate, and free tokens.</p>
          </li>

        </ul>

        <h3 class="subsection-title" data-animate="fade-up">Layer C — Advanced Capabilities</h3>
        <ul class="road-grid" role="list">

          <li class="road-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <h4 class="road-name">UDS Inbox</h4>
            <p class="road-layer">Layer 1 — Runtime</p>
            <p class="road-desc">Cross-session IPC via Unix domain sockets. Agents message each other without shared filesystem — persistent inbox survives restarts.</p>
          </li>

          <li class="road-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <h4 class="road-name">Bridge</h4>
            <p class="road-layer">Layer 8 — Remote</p>
            <p class="road-desc">Remote control via phone or browser. Manage terminal sessions, approve tool calls, and review diffs from the Flutter HPS Owner app.</p>
          </li>

          <li class="road-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <h4 class="road-name">/bughunter</h4>
            <p class="road-layer">Layer 2 — Orchestration</p>
            <p class="road-desc">Adversarial agent that probes your code for edge cases, race conditions, and logic bugs. Runs in parallel with normal development.</p>
          </li>

          <li class="road-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <h4 class="road-name">SKILL_SEARCH</h4>
            <p class="road-layer">Layer 2 — Orchestration</p>
            <p class="road-desc">Semantic vector search over the skill registry. Finds relevant skills by embedding similarity — powered by hps-ml and FTS5.</p>
          </li>

          <li class="road-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <h4 class="road-name">Injection Defense</h4>
            <p class="road-layer">Layer 7 — Security</p>
            <p class="road-desc">Six-layer prompt injection defense system. Detects and blocks injection attempts at input, tool-call, and output stages.</p>
          </li>

          <li class="road-card" data-animate="fade-up">
            <h4 class="road-name">/force-snip</h4>
            <p class="road-layer">Layer 4 — Memory</p>
            <p class="road-desc">Manual context token freeing. Snip older conversation turns to reclaim context window space — also unified into context-mode (Layer B).</p>
          </li>

        </ul>

      </div>
    </section>

    <CTASection
      title="From leaks to shipped features."
      lede="Every feature on the roadmap ties back to a concrete layer in the architecture."
    >
      <Fragment slot="cta">
        <Button href="/architecture" variant="primary" icon="lucide:arrow-right" iconPosition="end">Architecture</Button>
        <Button href="/news" variant="ghost" icon="lucide:newspaper">Changelog</Button>
      </Fragment>
    </CTASection>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ── Main wrapper ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .main {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  /* ── Content sections ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .content-section {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .section-inner {
    max-width: var(--container-max);
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-block: var(--space-24);
    padding-inline: var(--space-6);
  }

  .section-title {
    font-size: var(--font-size-2xl);
    font-weight: 300;
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-snug);
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-12);
  }

  .subsection-title {
    font-size: var(--font-size-lg);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: var(--space-16) 0 var(--space-8);
  }

  /* ── Prose ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .prose {
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: var(--content-max);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-8);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .prose strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* ── Leak grid — feature cards ─────────────────────────────────────── */

  .leak-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-4);
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-12);
    padding: 0;
  }

  .leak-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    transition: border-color var(--duration-quick) var(--ease-standard);
  }

  .leak-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-border-strong);
  }

  .leak-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .leak-name {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .status-badge {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: var(--space-0-5) var(--space-2);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    white-space: nowrap;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .status-badge[data-status="unreleased"] {
    border-color: var(--color-border-strong);
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
  }

  .status-badge[data-status="env-flag"] {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .status-badge[data-status="released"] {
    border-color: var(--color-success, var(--color-accent));
    color: var(--color-success, var(--color-accent));
  }

  .leak-desc {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
  }

  .leak-hps {
    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .leak-hps strong {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  /* ── Callouts ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .callout {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-6);
    margin: var(--space-8) 0;
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .callout p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .callout a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .callout-evergreen {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }

  /* ── Hidden Commands table ─────────────────────────────────────────── */

  .table-wrapper {
    overflow-x: auto;
    -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .cmd-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
  }

  .cmd-table th,
  .cmd-table td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .cmd-table th {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .cmd-table td {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .cmd-table code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    padding: var(--space-0-5) var(--space-1);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  /* ── Roadmap grid — future items ───────────────────────────────────── */

  .road-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-4);
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-8);
    padding: 0;
  }

  .road-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    transition: border-color var(--duration-quick) var(--ease-standard);
  }

  .road-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-border-strong);
  }

  .road-name {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--font-size-base);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-1);
  }

  .road-layer {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--font-size-xs);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
  }

  .road-desc {
    font-size: var(--font-size-sm);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
